==German==

===Etymology===
Old High German ''chuocho''.
Etymology unclear. Possibly related to several Romanic words (eg. Catalan ''[[coca]]'' “cake”), which are descendant from {{L.}} ''[[cochlea]]'' “[[snail]]”. Unrelated to ''[[Küche]]''.

===Noun===
'''Kuchen''' ''m'' (''genitive'' Kuchens, ''plural'' Kuchen)
# a [[cake]]
# milk-[[loaf]]

